    "extras": [
      "Cambodia uses USD almost everywhere, with riel given back as change; keep plenty of small notes for tuk-tuks, snacks, and tips.",
      "The official Angkor 3-day pass costs ₹5,208 and is the sweet spot for most first trips; buy it only from the official Angkor Ticket Centre.",
      "Download offline Google Maps before heading to Bokor or Koh Rong, and keep PassApp or Grab ready for airport and city rides.",
      "Withdraw enough cash before taking the Koh Rong ferry because island ATMs are unreliable to non-existent compared with mainland Cambodia.",
      "Cover shoulders and knees at Angkor temples, the Royal Palace, and Phnom Penh pagodas; lightweight linen works better than denim in the heat.",
      "If you were thinking of combining Thailand overland, re-check current border rules before leaving because land-border access can change faster than flight schedules."
